<p><b>Microtonal music</b> is <a href="/wiki/Music" title="Music">music</a> using <i>microtones</i> — <a href="/wiki/Musical_interval" title="Musical interval" class="mw-redirect">intervals</a> of less than an <a href="/wiki/Equal_Temperament" title="Equal Temperament" class="mw-redirect">equally spaced</a> <a href="/wiki/Semitone" title="Semitone">semitone</a>. <b>Microtonal music</b> can also refer to music which uses intervals not found in the Western system of 12 equal intervals to the octave.</p>
